<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Elon Musk=C2=A0theory of corporate governa=
nce is that everything that Elon Musk does is good for his investors:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Elon Musk has made many hundreds of b=
illions of dollars for investors in his various companies.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Those investor returns come, in large part, from M=
usk=E2=80=99s personal attributes and efforts: Those companies would not be=
 successful without=C2=A0his perfectionism, drive, management style, techno=
-optimism, etc.; nobody else could have built those companies, and even tod=
ay they would not perform nearly as well without Musk=E2=80=99s intense per=
sonal involvement.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Those personal =
attributes, which are good for investors, are inseparable from the rest of =
his personality, which is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0oh, you know. =E2=80=9CI reinvente=
d electric cars and I=E2=80=99m sending people to Mars in a rocket ship,=E2=
=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34726086.26=
0360/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj1xZ3VWUzFQVEdqOA/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cB48115998" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;">Musk once said</a> on=C2=A0<em>Saturday Nig=
ht Live</em>;=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cdid you think I was also going to be a chill, n=
ormal dude?=E2=80=9D His personality only works as a complete package; you =
can=E2=80=99t get the shareholder value creation without the bad tweets.</l=
i>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Therefore, the bad tweets are=C2=A0<=
em>also good</em>, because they enable the good stuff; they are the compost=
 that feeds the flowers of shareholder value.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This theory is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I mean, it=E2=80=
=99s probably not=C2=A0<em>wrong</em>, is it? It is pretty unhelpful as a t=
heory, though. It proves too much. It implies that any conflict of interest=
 between Musk and his shareholders is=C2=A0<em>impossible</em>, because wha=
tever Musk wants is necessarily good for shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0even i=
f it is=C2=A0<em>bad</em>=C2=A0for shareholders, it is good, because the ba=
d thing is just the price they pay for Musk=E2=80=99s goodness.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The most important application of this theory =
was probably when Musk asked Tesla Inc. to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/34726086.260360/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS=
