" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">mused</a> that he might need=C2=A0<em=
>another=C2=A0</em>$50 billion to keep doing it. A Delaware judge struck do=
wn that pay package, finding that there was a conflict of interest (Musk co=
ntrolled the board of directors that awarded him the pay) and that the pay =
was too much. Delaware does not subscribe to the Elon Musk theory of corpor=
ate governance.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgrou=
nd-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a> In that theory, there can be no conflict of interest, and no amount of=
 pay that is too much, because anything that Elon Musk wants is necessarily=
 in the best interests of shareholders.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/34726086.260360/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMTgvbXVzay1zYXlzLWtldGFtaW5lLXByZXNjcmlwdGl=
vbi1pcy1pbi1pbnZlc3RvcnMtYmVzdC1pbnRlcmVzdHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMxODI0X01PTkVZU1=
RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwM=
zE4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBffeb13e1" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">Elon Musk on the Elon Musk theory</a> of corporate governance:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk said that his prescribed use of keta=
mine alleviates periods of low mood and is in the best interest of investor=
s in Tesla Inc. and the other companies he runs.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For Wall Street, =E2=80=9Cwhat matters is exec=
ution,=E2=80=9D Musk said in an interview with former CNN anchor Don Lemon =
streamed Monday on YouTube. =E2=80=9CFrom an investor standpoint, if there =
is something I=E2=80=99m taking, I should keep taking it,=E2=80=9D he said =
referring to Tesla=E2=80=99s success.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk said he takes the drug as prescribed peri=
odically to treat what he described as =E2=80=9Cchemical tides=E2=80=9D tha=
t lead to depression-like symptoms.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am sure Elon Musk has good doctors, and I am=
 not going to second-guess the <em>medical </em>advice he is getting, but t=
he=C2=A0<em>corporate governance=C2=A0</em>theory here is =E2=80=9Cif there=
=E2=80=99s something I=E2=80=99m taking, I should keep taking it.=E2=80=9D =
That logic applies to taking ketamine on medical advice, or taking cocaine =
against medical advice, or anything else. Whatever he does is necessarily g=
ood.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One could quibble. Tesla=E2=80=99s stock peake=
d in November 2021. Arguably everything Musk did=C2=A0<em>up to=C2=A0</em>t=
hat point created hundreds of billions of dollars of shareholder value; eve=
